In this proclamation, President Donald Trump declares November 22 through November 28, 2020, as National Family Week. He emphasizes the importance of families in strengthening communities and shaping values. The proclamation highlights the actions taken by the Trump administration to support families during the coronavirus pandemic, such as providing economic relief through the CARES Act and expanding paid family, medical, and sick leave. The President also mentions efforts to improve mental health services and the progress made in developing and distributing vaccines. Trump pledges to continue supporting families by ensuring access to childcare, paid family leave, school choice, and job training. He concludes by expressing gratitude for families and calling for ceremonies and activities to honor them during this week.